text: Mateo de Toro Zambrano y Ureta, I Count of La Conquista (September 20, 1727 - February 26, 1811), was a Spanish military and political figure of Criollo descent. He held the position of a knight in the Order of Santiago and was the lord of the Toro-Zambrano estate. He was also the President of Chile.
